Article Headline: Wednesday Wins the Week — Season 2 Snaps Its Way to No. 1 in Top 10
Article SubHeadline: KPop Demon Huntersclimbs on Most Popular, fans swoon overMy Oxford Year.
Article Data: As though returning to the scene of the crime andknowing where the bodies are buried, woeful watchers everywhere returned to Nevermore Academy in droves, effortlessly catapulting Part 1 ofWednesdaySeason 2 to the top of theEnglish TV Listwith an electrifying 50 million views.The first four episodes of Season 2 saw the second most views in a single week across all English TV, behindWednesdaySeason 1. Plus, Season 2, Part 1 now holds the record for English TV title ranked No. 1 in most countries (91 total) in its first week. In Part 1 of this season, the mirthless mystery-solver Wednesday (Jenna Ortega) investigates a string of puzzling new murders as she contends with the challenge of mastering her psychic abilities, unmasking a sadistic stalker, and racing against the clock to prevent the death of her best friend, Enid (Emma Myers).WednesdaySeason 1 also made an appearance on the list, landing at No. 2 with 8.6 million views, bringing viewers up to speed for the new school year. Fans of literary romance took a trip across the pond to study Victorian poetry, and fell head over heels forMy Oxford Year. Viewers couldn’t help but swoon over theSofia Carson and Corey Mylchreest–starringromantic drama, which claimed the No. 1 spot on theEnglish Film Listand became a Top 10 hit in all countries ranked after amassing another 27.2 million views in its second week. Week after week, the musical animated original filmKPop Demon Huntershas taken over the world, one K-pop bop at a time — and with no signs of slowing down. The K-pop trio HUNTR/X continued to sing their way into the hearts of audiences everywhere, earning another 25.9 million views to remain steady at No. 2 on the English Film List, while also rising to No. 2 on theMost Popular list. KPop Demon Hunters A Sing-Along Event,a series of screenings across the US and Canada on August 23 and 24, will give fans a chance to sing along to their favorite tunes on the big screen, like the song of the summer “Golden,” which climbed to the No. 1 spot on theBillboardHot 100 chartlast week. The song has also spent four nonconsecutive weeks atop theBillboardglobal charts. Also in English film, Golf’s favorite underdog wasn’t done with his comeback tour just yet.Happy Gilmore 2remained a hit among fans of Adam Sandler’s beloved linksman, earning him a spot on the list at No. 3 with 14.7 million views. Like the view from the top of El Capitan,UNTAMEDheld its place among the metaphorical clouds of the English TV List, now in the No. 3 spot with 7.2 million views. Audiences pursued justice with Agent Turner (Eric Bana) as he tracked down a killer in the wilds of Yosemite. For an entirely different sort of “wild,” viewers braved the boozy brunches and power dynamics of Texas society inThe Hunting Wives, landing the series in the No. 4 spot with another 4.7 million views. Proving the unstoppable power of thewrestling worldwas Monday’s WWERAWlive event. Fresh off an eventful SummerSlam weekend, the exciting showdown between Rusev and Sheamus bodyslammed the No. 5 spot with 3 million views. With steamy suspense, anotherdesperate wifeintrigued watchers as the Mexican dramaUnspeakable Sinstook the No. 1 spot on theNon-English TV Listwith 6.2 million views. Desperate to escape her abusive marriage, Helena (Zuria Vega) and her lover Iván (Andrés Baida) scheme to blackmail her husband, but the plan goes terribly wrong, leading Helena into a fight for survival. Landing in the No. 2 spot was Korean courtroom dramaBeyond the Bar, which follows rookie lawyer Kang Hyo-min (Jung Chae-yeon) as she navigates her new role taking on complex cases at a top law firm. DAN DA DANused its supernatural powers to land the No. 3 spot on the Non-English TV list with 2.5 million views. Meanwhile, the South African high-stakes thrillerMarkedpushed its way to No. 4 on the list, also with 2.5 million views. The series follows a desperate mother, Babalwa (Lerato Mvelase), who grapples with her morals and her need to aid her sick daughter, no matter the cost. Last week,non-English filmwas all about European thrillers. Audienceswere locked inon the German mystery-thrillerBrick, which claimed the No. 1 spot with another 2.3 million views. The film was joined by fellow German thriller,Exterritorial, which brought plenty of action at No. 9 (1 million views). Then, fans were swept off their feet by the “anarchistic love story” at the center of Swedish crime thriller,An Honest Life(No. 2, 2.3 million views), followed by the 2022 Italian action-crime thrillerMy Name Is Vendetta(No. 3, 2 million views). Smart, sarcastic and a little dead inside, Wednesday Addams investigates twisted mysteries while making new friends — and foes — at Nevermore Academy.

Article Headline: Kevin Hart and Netflix Are Looking for America’s Next Big Comedian
Article SubHeadline: The competition will be no joke, and casting is open now.
Article Data: Whether you’re the type who loves watching stand-up and laughing until your sides hurt, or you’ve got the nerve to step onstage and tell jokes in front of a live audience, this one’s for you: Netflix just announced a new series that actuallyisa laughing matter. In 2026, global superstarKevin Hartwill executive produce a new comedy series alongside comic heavyweights (to be announced at a later date). Together, they’ll guide contestants through an unfiltered, uncensored, and unapologetic competition that pulls back the curtain on the gritty, hilarious, and often unpredictable path of a stand-up career. Over the course of the eight-episode series, contestants from all over the US will face rigorous tests that mirror the real-life journey of a comedian, from brutal open mics to bombed sets and rewrites to the pressure of big-stage performances. The competition will give viewers an unvarnished look at comedy’s darkest corners and brightest spotlights with challenges inspired by some of the comics’ actual career trajectories. Kevin Hart is joined by executive producers Jane Lipsitz, Dan Cutforth, Nan Strait and Dan Volpe to Alfred Street credits (Alfred Street Industries) and Luke Kelly-Clyne and Meghan Hoffman (Hartbeat). Alfred Street, founded in 2019 by Emmy-winning producers Cutforth and Lipsitz, is known for series includingNext Gen Chef,Homicide: Los Angeles,Is It Cake?,and the Emmy Award–winningSparking Joy with Marie Kondo. Hartbeat — founded by Kevin Hart — is a global, multi-platform entertainment company creating content and experiences at the intersection of comedy and culture, with a mission to keep the world laughing together. Its signature stand-up projects include the global showcase Comedy in Color (featuring over 300 comedians from 30+ countries), Hulu’s LOL Live, the recent revival of Comic View on BET, and stand-up series for London Hughes, Affion Crockett, and the late David A. Arnold. Hartbeat also launched Women Write Now, a career incubator for the next generation of Black women in comedy both onstage and behind the camera. This upcoming competition continues Hartbeat’s commitment to championing emerging comedic voices. The series premieres on Netflix in 2026. Think you’ve got what it takes?Apply here now for your chance to be America’s next great comedian, and be sure to check back with Tudum for future updates.

Article Headline: Before Taylor Swift’s The Life of a Showgirl, There Was Miss Americana
Article SubHeadline: The singer-songwriter gets real in the first-ever documentary about her life.
Article Data: If you’re looking to relive some of your favoriteTaylor Swift momentsnow that the singer hasannounced her upcoming album,The Life of a Showgirl, it’s about time to visit (or revisit) the 2020 documentaryMiss Americana.The film — by Emmy-winning director Lana Wilson (Pretty Baby: Brooke Shields,After Tiller) — is a snapshot of the pop culture icon during a transformational period in her life, and documents Swift’s nearly two decades in the limelight before herrecord-breakingErastour. From her preteen performances to her2018Reputationtourto penning her 2019 albumLover, the documentary shows Swift reflecting on her upbringing, her values, the pressures of fame, and her sprawling career achievements. Stream it now. Scroll up to the top of this article and check it out. The documentary revolves around Swift, a 12-time Grammy winner and 40-time American Music Award winner. The film also features Panic! At The Disco lead singer Brendon Urie; Swift’s mother, Andrea Swift; record producer and musician Jack Antonoff; and actor and Swift’s then-partner, Joe Alwyn. The film documents Swift creating songs for her 2019 albumLoverat Electric Lady Studios in New York City, reflecting on her rise to fame and her songwriting process, and grappling with missing out on Grammy noms following the release of 2017’sReputation. Amidst footage from her first concerts as a child, her 2006 self-titled debut album release, and her 2018Reputationtour, Swift looks back on how she’s become who she’s become, the adversity she’s faced, and how her opinions of herself — and her outspokenness on divisive political issues — has changed. The film also features Swift’s original song “Only the Young,” which she wrote and recorded to coincide with the documentary’s release. Themusic documentarytakes place in a number of locations Swift frequents, like her New York City apartment, her Nashville home, and NYC’s legendary recording studio Electric Lady Studios. In this revealing documentary, Taylor Swift embraces her role as a songwriter and performer — and as a woman harnessing the full power of her voice.

Article Headline: New Unknown Number Trailer Unveils the Shocking Real Story of Teen Cyberbullying
Article SubHeadline: A high school romance turns into a social media nightmare.
Article Data: The next explosive true crime documentary from director Skye Borgman (Girl in the Picture,Abducted in Plain Sight) begins with a single, unsettling text message from a blocked number.Unknown Number: The High School Catfish, premiering Aug. 29, delves into a harrowing case of cyberbullying that sends a small town into chaos. The film follows a teenage girl and her boyfriend, who become the targets of relentless harassment from an anonymous phone number. As authorities dig deeper into the months-long ordeal, they uncover a secret that challenges everything they originally believed about the case. Unknown Number: The High School Catfishis directed by Skye Borgman, produced by Ross M. Dinerstein and Rebecca Evans, and executive produced by Borgman, Ross Girard, Tom Forman, David Metzler, Justin Sprague, and Alysia Sofios. The film is produced by Campfire Studios in association with Terminal B TV. Vulgar, taunting texts blow up the phones of a teen and her boyfriend. Who's sending them — and why? This twisty documentary reveals the shocking answer.
